00:38:58,795 --> 00:39:00,463
(ABE) You got out too soon.

642
00:39:02,090 --> 00:39:05,343
You have to wait for the stopwatch
so that you know the gain is low enough.

643
00:39:06,302 --> 00:39:07,679
So, we're back here?

644
00:39:08,471 --> 00:39:11,933
Yeah, we're here.
It's 8:50, Tuesday morning.

645
00:39:16,271 --> 00:39:18,189
All right. Give me a few minutes.

646
00:39:21,442 --> 00:39:24,988
(ABE) From there it was easy.
The bulk of the work was done.

647
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:26,715
I just left everything the way I found it.

648
00:39:26,739 --> 00:39:29,701
I left the machine alone
and didn't turn it off or anything,

649
00:39:29,826 --> 00:39:31,119
and just cleared out of there.

650
00:39:31,244 --> 00:39:33,872
(AARON) OK, so that way,
your double would find everything

651
00:39:33,997 --> 00:39:35,999
exactly the same later that day
and get in the box?

652
00:39:36,124 --> 00:39:39,252
Right, right, but also, at that point,
I or my double or someone

653
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:40,657
was in the box coming backwards.

654
00:39:40,753 --> 00:39:43,923
So who knows what that would've done
if I would have turned the machine off.

655
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:46,509
(AARON) Definitely. Definitely.
So, they're one-time use only.

656
00:39:46,634 --> 00:39:51,055
So then, at that moment, since my double
was on the way to the hotel room in my car,

657
00:39:51,180 --> 00:39:54,559
I had to take a taxi home. But when we go,
we'll be able to use your truck.

658
00:40:15,622 --> 00:40:19,250
- You have a margin account, right?
